<br>
The only hard part is the &quot;T&quot; intersection before her hallway. Nasty either way you go, so we just Invis Undead and take the long way to save time. Just watch out for The Raid Ender nearby. It's a carpet that someone always falls into, and usually you are so far into East at the time that people get bored and want to end the raid rather than hangout and try again. Mobs will also summon you over the carpet occasionally if you pull them nearby. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ureegor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reegor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:00:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3273.topic&index=142>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3rd Chardok ring is shoulders/arms/wrist item (SOLVED)</span><hr size=1> Well, the nice thing about sarnak collective faction is that you can farm it in WW or loio or any other zone in kunark with goblins, as far as I can tell.  Most of FM (besides the raiders and such), Droga, and Nurga don't seem to work for collective faction, though.<br>
